note
; @pos 73 -30
; @stop 2 15 top @hidden

; MOD is a classic tracker music format
; from the 16-bit home-computer era.
; Tracker music is written as rows of events.
; Each row encodes what to do next, 
; such as which audio sample to play, 
; at what pitch, and which effect to apply.
noteEnd

note
; @pos 404 -17
; @stop 11 5 top @hidden
;                         
; The samples are selected 
; based on the sample number
; extracted from the active row.
noteEnd

note
; @pos 420 34
